AI4ALL Final Project: Hybrid LSTM-Embedding Neural Network for AQI Prediction

This project aims to predict the Air Quality Index (AQI) by integrating temporal and categorical data using a hybrid deep learning approach. The model combines LSTM layers to process sequential data (e.g., pollutant levels over time) and embedding layers to handle categorical features (e.g., state, county, and city). By leveraging this multi-input architecture, the model provides accurate AQI predictions based on historical pollutant levels and meteorological data.

Authors: Uyen Nguyen, Neha Janardhan, Nurbu Lama, Ignacio Ruiz

Last Update: 2024/12/29

In[87]:
# Prepare sequences for temporal data
def create_sequences(data, target, sequence_length=30):
    X, y = [], []
    for i in range(len(data) - sequence_length):
        X.append(data.iloc[i:i + sequence_length][features_columns].values)
        y.append(target.iloc[i + sequence_length]) 
    return np.array(X), np.array(y)

sequence_length = 30
train_X, train_y = create_sequences(train_data, train_data[target_column], sequence_length)
test_X, test_y = create_sequences(test_data, test_data[target_column], sequence_length)
In[88]:
# Prepare spatial feature arrays
train_states = train_data.iloc[sequence_length:]['State Encoded'].values
test_states = test_data.iloc[sequence_length:]['State Encoded'].values

train_counties = train_data.iloc[sequence_length:]['County Encoded'].values
test_counties = test_data.iloc[sequence_length:]['County Encoded'].values

train_cities = train_data.iloc[sequence_length:]['City Encoded'].values
test_cities = test_data.iloc[sequence_length:]['City Encoded'].values

b. Model Preparation

In[89]:
# Input for temporal data
temporal_input = Input(shape=(train_X.shape[1], train_X.shape[2]), name="Temporal_Input")

# LSTM layers
lstm_out = LSTM(256, return_sequences=True)(temporal_input)
lstm_out = Dropout(0.3)(lstm_out)
lstm_out = LSTM(128, return_sequences=True)(lstm_out)
lstm_out = Dropout(0.2)(lstm_out)
lstm_out = LSTM(64)(lstm_out)
lstm_out = Dropout(0.2)(lstm_out)

# Inputs for spatial features
state_input = Input(shape=(1,), name="State_Input")
county_input = Input(shape=(1,), name="County_Input")
city_input = Input(shape=(1,), name="City_Input")

# Embedding layers
state_embedding = Embedding(input_dim=len(state_encoder.classes_), output_dim=16)(state_input)
state_embedding = Flatten()(state_embedding)

county_embedding = Embedding(input_dim=len(county_encoder.classes_), output_dim=16)(county_input)
county_embedding = Flatten()(county_embedding)

city_embedding = Embedding(input_dim=len(city_encoder.classes_), output_dim=16)(city_input)
city_embedding = Flatten()(city_embedding)

# Concatenate spatial embeddings
spatial_out = Concatenate()([state_embedding, county_embedding, city_embedding])

# Combine temporal and spatial outputs
combined = Concatenate()([lstm_out, spatial_out])

# Dense layers for feature extraction
dense_out = Dense(128, activation='relu')(combined)
dense_out = Dropout(0.3)(dense_out)
dense_out = Dense(64, activation='relu')(dense_out)

# Final output layer
output = Dense(1, activation='linear', name="AQI_Output")(dense_out)

# Build and compile the model
model = Model(inputs=[temporal_input, state_input, county_input, city_input], outputs=output)
model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mean_squared_error')

# Model summary
model.summary()
